\section{Light Baryon Sector: First-Principles Mass-Hierarchy Correction}
\label{app:light_correction}

\subsection{Overview}

The light baryon sector exhibits systematic errors that grow with 
strangeness content (Table~\ref{tab:light_errors}). These errors arise 
from two physical effects that we derive from first principles using 
only quark masses and flux-tube tension—\textbf{no fitting to baryon masses}.

